WEBVTT

00:03.169 --> 00:05.296
KELLY:
<i>Good morning.</i>

00:05.380 --> 00:08.675
{\an4}Mm.
Hey, did Noah spend the night
here again last night?

00:08.758 --> 00:11.594
{\an4}Mm-hmm.
Oh, that makes...
three times in a row.

00:11.678 --> 00:13.012
Really?
I wasn't keeping track.

00:13.096 --> 00:14.431
Well, neither have I.

00:14.514 --> 00:16.891
{\an3}I just know that he's moving
off the boat this week.

00:16.975 --> 00:18.935
And I bet you're wondering
if he's moving in here.

00:19.018 --> 00:19.936
No.

00:20.019 --> 00:21.980
Yeah, I was a little curious.

00:22.063 --> 00:23.231
{\an1}So am I.

00:23.314 --> 00:24.858
{\an3}You don't know
where he's moving?

00:24.941 --> 00:26.609
Moving?

00:26.693 --> 00:28.611
I don't even know
what he's feeling.

00:28.695 --> 00:29.904
How are <i> you</i> feeling?

00:29.988 --> 00:32.573
I just... I feel like

00:32.656 --> 00:35.785
I really want to take care
of him, you know?

00:35.869 --> 00:38.329
Ding-dong! Hey, Donna,
you have those revisions?

00:38.413 --> 00:40.290
(gasps)
Revisions, deadline, oh!

00:40.373 --> 00:41.958
Hi.

00:42.041 --> 00:43.001
{\an1}DONNA:
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:43.084 --> 00:44.502
Carrie Knox, Kelly Taylor.

00:44.586 --> 00:46.963
{\an4}Kelly's my roommate,
and Carrie I hired
to help me with

00:47.046 --> 00:47.922
{\an3}my sketch revisions.
Nice to meet you.

00:48.006 --> 00:49.299
Nice meeting you.

00:49.382 --> 00:50.300
(sighs)

00:50.383 --> 00:52.302
You know, why they need
revisions is a mystery.

00:52.385 --> 00:54.554
I mean, your originals
are very rad.

00:54.637 --> 00:55.972
God, if I had
your talent...

00:56.055 --> 00:58.475
It would be a huge step
backwards, but nice try.

00:58.558 --> 01:00.810
Okay, I got 'em.

01:00.894 --> 01:03.313
Great, so then I have
the sketches in order,

01:03.396 --> 01:04.980
plus copy, plus
cost breakdown.

01:05.063 --> 01:05.815
Great. Good work.

01:05.899 --> 01:07.525
This could be
my big breakthrough.

01:07.609 --> 01:09.486
So, are you gonna take
the 10 or Venice?

01:09.569 --> 01:12.322
{\an4}I'll make my deadline;
you just remember
to make yours.

01:12.405 --> 01:14.866
{\an6}(sighs)
Lunch with Jankowski
should seal the deal.

01:14.949 --> 01:16.826
{\an3}I'm gone.
Bye.

01:16.910 --> 01:18.286
Good morning,
good morning.

01:18.369 --> 01:19.829
{\an1}Coffee, anyone?
Ah. Yes.

01:19.913 --> 01:21.080
Thank you.
Okay.

01:21.164 --> 01:24.000
No, thank you, I already have
some-- but thank you for that

01:24.083 --> 01:26.002
{\an6}job recommendation.
Oh, that means
you got my message.

01:26.085 --> 01:27.337
I wouldn't let
this one get away.

01:27.420 --> 01:30.840
{\an6}Actually, I'm very
comfortable being
undirected right now.

01:30.924 --> 01:33.176
Okay.

01:33.259 --> 01:33.843
All set?

01:33.927 --> 01:35.845
Let's go.

01:35.929 --> 01:37.806
{\an3}Hey, excuse me.
Good morning.

01:37.889 --> 01:40.558
{\an5}Where you going?
Pasadena, to get
my dad's stuff.

01:40.642 --> 01:43.019
{\an3}Okay, um, I'll
give you a ride.

01:43.102 --> 01:44.020
No, it's covered.

01:44.103 --> 01:45.230
{\an3}I want to.

01:45.313 --> 01:46.898
I know, and I appreciate it.

01:46.981 --> 01:48.358
I'm gonna go with Brandon.

01:49.609 --> 01:51.402
Sure.

01:52.904 --> 01:55.114
{\an1}Ready?
Yeah.

01:56.241 --> 01:58.535
What?

02:01.454 --> 02:03.373
I want him to live with me.

02:03.456 --> 02:04.833
Then tell him.

02:05.834 --> 02:07.252
{\an3}Uh-uh.

02:07.335 --> 02:09.878
{\an3}Brandon, you forgot
your ph...

02:09.963 --> 02:12.090
phone.

02:17.512 --> 02:19.430
{\an1}I want you to write
the obituary.

02:19.514 --> 02:21.599
{\an3}Whoa, whoa, whoa, you
got the wrong guy, buddy.

02:21.683 --> 02:25.353
{\an5}My plate's full as it is.
All the other papers
want to write is:

02:25.436 --> 02:26.604
{\an1}Daniel Hunter,
businessman, legend.

02:26.688 --> 02:27.856
And this is a <i> bad</i> thing?

02:27.939 --> 02:31.442
When honoring a man, it usually
involves telling the truth.

02:31.526 --> 02:32.777
{\an1}What, your father
<i>wasn't</i> a legend?

02:32.861 --> 02:34.737
You gonna write
the piece or not?

02:34.821 --> 02:37.407
Help you?
Yeah, I'm Daniel Hunter's son.

02:37.490 --> 02:40.410
I'm here to get his things.

02:45.331 --> 02:46.708
Plastic bag.

02:46.791 --> 02:48.501
How suitably transparent.

02:50.962 --> 02:52.881
You're giving me his gun?

02:52.964 --> 02:53.923
This some kind
of sick joke?

02:54.007 --> 02:56.384
My father blew his brains out
with that thing.

02:56.467 --> 02:57.886
{\an3}I understand your
suffering, sir,

02:57.969 --> 02:59.888
{\an3}but this is
not a warehouse.

02:59.971 --> 03:03.057
{\an5}So what am I gonna do,
hang it on my wall?
Hey, come on, let's go.

03:03.141 --> 03:05.685
I'm asking you a question!
Come on, let's go.

03:09.022 --> 03:11.566
It's okay. Let's go.

